quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  37,1,"By those aligned, lined up in ranks."
  37,2,"Then by the propellers propelling firmly."
  37,3,"Then by the readers of a Reminder—"
  37,4,"indeed, your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>God is surely One,"
  37,5,"Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them, and Lord of the Easts."
  37,6,"Indeed, We have adorned the lowest{1}heaven <span class=""h"">with</span><span class=""h"">an adornment, the planets<sup foot_note=""80963"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>,",footnotes:1:The Arabic word dunyatranslated here as ‘lowest’ is the same word used to describe the life of this world as the ‘Earlier’ Life, as it carries both meanings: lowest and earlier.
  37,7,"and as a protection against every defiant devil."
  37,8,"They cannot <span class=""h"">eavesdrop<sup foot_note=""80964"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">on</span>the Higher Assembly, for they get bombarded from every side—"
  37,9,"repelled, and they will have an unremitting punishment,"
  37,10,"except for one who snatched a fragment and was then pursued by a piercing meteor."
  37,11,"So inquire<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>of them, “Are they more difficult to create, or the others We created?” Indeed, We created them from sticky clay."
  37,12,"Rather, <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a><span class=""h"">were amazed<sup foot_note=""80965"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">as</span>they ridicule."
  37,13,"And when reminded, they remember not."
  37,14,"And when they see a sign, they exaggerate in ridiculing"
  37,15,"and say, “This is nothing but evident sorcery."
  37,16,"<span class=""h"">Can it be that</span>when we have died and become dust and bones, <span class=""h"">can it be that<sup foot_note=""80966"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>we will really be resurrected?"
  37,17,"<span class=""h"">And<sup foot_note=""80967"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>our ancient forefathers?”"
  37,18,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Yes indeed, and you will be totally subdued.”"
  37,19,"It is but a single nudge, and there they are looking on<i class=""s"">(in bewilderment) </i>!"
  37,20,"And they said{1}, “Woe to us! This is the Day of Recompense.”",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered upon by the reader.
  37,21,"“This is the Day of Decision which you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>used to deny."
  37,22,"Herd<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>those who were unjust and their spouses, and what they used to worship"
  37,23,"apart from Allah, and guide them to the path to purgatory."
  37,24,"And stop them—indeed, they are to be questioned.”"
